    "15": {
      "answer": "Better scalability – statistical systems can learn from large datasets without manually writing rules. Higher robustness/flexibility – they handle ambiguity and unseen cases better than rigid rule-based systems.",
      "answered_at": "2026-04-25T08:43:22.350Z",
      "date": "2026-04-25",
      "time": "10:43:22"
    },
    "17": {
      "answer": "Word vectors (e.g., Word2Vec) are static, meaning the same word always has the same representation, regardless of context. They do not capture sentence structure or meaning.  For tasks like sentiment analysis or QA, contextual models (e.g., BERT, GPT) and sequence models (RNNs, LSTMs, Transformers) are used because they consider context.",
      "answered_at": "2026-04-25T08:43:22.350Z",
